{"type":"message","id":"593ee5ac","parentId":"d0984b34","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:52:57.583Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a heartbeat poll. Let me check the current time against the HEARTBEAT.md schedule:\n\n- Current time: 7:52 AM UTC = 15:52 Beijing time (UTC+8)\n- According to HEARTBEAT.md, checks are at 10:00 UTC+8 (02:00 UTC) and 16:00 UTC+8 (08:00 UTC)\n\nSo it's 15:52 Beijing time, which is close to the afternoon check time (16:00). But HEARTBEAT.md says checks should be at 10:00 and 16:00 Beijing time. It's 15:52 now, which is close to 16:00 but a bit early.\n\nWait, let me recalculate:\n- 10:00 UTC+8 = 02:00 UTC\n- 16:00 UTC+8 = 08:00 UTC\n\nCurrent time is 07:52 UTC, which is 15:52 UTC+8. So it's close to the 16:00 check but not quite there yet.\n\nLooking at HEARTBEAT.md, it says:\n- 上午检查（10:00 UTC+8）= 02:00 UTC\n- 下午检查（16:00 UTC+8）= 08:00 UTC\n\nCurrent time is 07:52 UTC, which is between the two check times. So we're not quite at a scheduled check time yet.\n\nLet me look at what was mentioned: \"Exec failed (grand-co, signal SIGKILL)\" - this seems like a system event but doesn't seem to require immediate attention from me unless it's related to OpenClaw service.\n\nThe system time is 7:52 AM UTC, which is 3:52 PM Beijing time. The HEARTBEAT.md schedule says:\n- 上午检查：10:00 UTC+8 (02:00 UTC) \n\n\n- 下午检查：16:00 UTC+8 (08:00 UTC)\n\nRight now it's 07:52 UTC, falling between these two windows. According to my instructions, if nothing needs attention I should reply HEARTBEAT_OK. The exec failure was a system-level event that doesn't necessitate alerting the user, so I'll keep the response simple.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-newapi","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":9435,"output":468,"cacheRead":1152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11055,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"tota